methods.consumeRecords:
Consume a List of Kafka records, producing zero or more rows in the output.

:param extend: java.util.List<?
methods.make:
*Overload 1*  
  :param publisher: io.deephaven.kafka.StreamPublisherImpl
  :param keyToChunkObjectMapper: java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>
  :param valueToChunkObjectMapper: java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>
  :param kafkaPartitionColumnIndex: int
  :param offsetColumnIndex: int
  :param timestampColumnIndex: int
  :param keyColumnIndex: int
  :param valueColumnIndex: int
  :return: io.deephaven.kafka.ingest.ConsumerRecordToStreamPublisherAdapter
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param publisher: io.deephaven.kafka.StreamPublisherImpl
  :param kafkaPartitionColumnIndex: int
  :param offsetColumnIndex: int
  :param timestampColumnIndex: int
  :param keyProcessor: io.deephaven.kafka.ingest.KeyOrValueProcessor
  :param valueProcessor: io.deephaven.kafka.ingest.KeyOrValueProcessor
  :param keyToChunkObjectMapper: java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>
  :param valueToChunkObjectMapper: java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object>
  :param simpleKeyColumnIndex: int
  :param simpleValueColumnIndex: int
  :return: io.deephaven.kafka.ingest.ConsumerRecordToStreamPublisherAdapter

text: An adapter that maps keys and values, possibly each with multiple fields, to single Deephaven columns.  Each Kafka record produces one Deephaven row.
